      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Coleman D. Bennett, also known as Colonel Coleman Bennett,
         was born in Bedford County, Virginia in 1806, the son of
         Richard and Asenath Sena Dalton Bennett. As an adult Bennett
         took residence in Pittsylvania Court House, Virginia, where he
         achieved financial success as a merchant and banker. Bennett
         also earned a moderate level of civic prominence serving as
         Pittsylvania County postmaster and sheriff and later as a
         Pittsylvania County representative in the Virginia legislature
         for the session 1842-1843. He married first Sarah Smith Jones
         on 11 Dec. 1834 and second Martha Ann Parrish circa 1843.
         Coleman D. Bennett died in 1870.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Receipts, 4 March 1864, of Coleman D. Bennett (1806-1870),
         Pittsylvania County's sheriff, issued by C. P. Hyde of the
         Headquarters Engineer Department, Department of Northern
         Virginia for the delivery of H. A. Berger's slave named
         Clanton and T. J. Hodnett's slave named Isaac.</p>
      </scopecontent>
